{
  "id": "xasset_defensive_breadth",
  "thesis": "Cross-asset defensive asset allocation (DAA): each month score every asset with a 13612W average-momentum (front-weighted 1/3/6/12-month returns). A canary breadth gate (SPY, HYG, IWM) sets the cash fraction = share of canaries with non-positive momentum, de-risking before the held asset confirms a downtrend. The risk-on book holds the top-2 offensive equity ETFs (SPY/QQQ/IWM/XLK); the defensive book holds the top defensive asset (TLT/GLD/HYG) only if its own momentum is positive, else cash \u2014 avoiding the 2022 forced-long-bonds trap. Net exposure floats in [0,1]. Crucially, an ensemble across staggered month-end rebalance offsets (0/5/10/15) is averaged to neutralize rebalance timing luck and smooth turnover by ~4x.",
